Uses of Package
prac02_ex3

Classes in prac02_ex3 used by prac02_ex3
Hero
          A feature common to all the comic book heroes of interest in this exercise is that they have (at least) two identities, a "super" one used when performing heroic feats and a "plain" one that allows them to move through society without attracting attention.
SuperHero
          A superhero is a hero (with two identities) but may also have superpowers.
SuperPower
          This enumerated type lists super powers commonly available to comic book superheroes and associates a (subjective) value with each one for defeating supervillains.
